      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 constructs from production lot; dimensional inspection confirms specimens within nominal tolerance; two independent laboratories provide inter-lab variability estimate.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from production components. CMM inspection confirms all specimens within ±0.05 mm of nominal. Testing split across two independent laboratories (FDA CDRH and DePuy Synthes) to characterize inter-lab variability (CV < 4%)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span at least two load levels or two construct configurations to confirm model predictive range; environmental conditions (temperature, humidity) documented.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single ASTM F1717 standard condition (5 mm/min displacement rate, ambient temperature). Only one construct configuration (7.5 mm non-cannulated) evaluated. Achieved level 2 is below required level 3; this factor is identified as a gap. Compensating evidence: E/uval metric remains below 1.96 threshold despite single-condition limitation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions and material inputs demonstrably equivalent to experimental test setup; any deviations documented and uncertainty contribution quantified.",
      "rationale": "Fixture geometry, torque preload on set screws (4 Nm per protocol), and vertebral body block material (UHMWPE per F1717) replicated in FEA. Deviations: idealized block geometry vs. machined block — sensitivity analysis shows <1% QoI effect. Full equivalency documented in modeling report."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10% for all three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement).",
      "rationale": "Stiffness: FEA 187 N/mm vs. experimental mean 192 N/mm (2.6% difference, E/uval=0.71). Yield force: FEA 412 N vs. experimental mean 421 N (2.1% difference, E/uval=0.58). Force at 40 mm: FEA 638 N vs. experimental mean 651 N (2.0% difference, E/uval=0.63). All QoIs meet acceptance criteria."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
