      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements under ASTM F1717.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the anterior column; yield force is the primary regulatory endpoint for fatigue risk assessment; force at 40 mm displacement characterizes post-yield behavior relevant to intraoperative failure risk. All three QoIs are standard F1717 endpoints and directly relevant to the COU."
