    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is compensated by the strong quantitative output comparison results (all QoIs within 3% of experimental mean, E/uval < 0.75) and the direct relevance of the validation scenario to the COU. Overall credibility is sufficient to support regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending.",
